'''Cristian Gabriel Romero''' (born 27 April 1998)<ref>{{cite web |last=Dawes |first=Olly |date=17 December 2022 |title=Why is Cristian Romero called Cuti? Tottenham star's nickname explained |url=https://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2022/12/17/why-is-cristian-romero-called-cuti-tottenham-argentina/ |access-date=17 September 2023 |website=HITC}}</ref> is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|TottenhH}} club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], whom he [[Captain (association football)|captains]], and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

Coming through the youth system, Romero began his senior career in 2016 at [[Club Atlético Belgrano|Belgrano]]. He moved to Italy in 2018, playing for [[Genoa CFC|Genoa]]. Romero was purchased by [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] the following season; he was sent back on loan to Genoa before being sent on loan to [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] in 2020. After being named [[Serie A Awards|Serie A's Best Defender]] for the [[2020–21 Serie A#Seasonal awards|2020–21 season]], the club exercised the option of purchase, before promptly loaning Romero to Tottenham with an obligation to buy. After a successful loan spell, Romero was signed by Tottenham in 2022, and went on to win the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League]].

Romero represented Argentina at the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|youth level]] at the [[2017 South American U-20 Championship]]. He made his senior debut in 2021 and was a key member of the squads that won the [[2021 Copa América]], [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], and [[2024 Copa América]].

==Club career==
===Belgrano===
Having joined the youth team in 2014,<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|date=6 May 2019|title=Cristian Romero: la scheda tecnica|url=https://jmania.it/cristian-romero-scheda-tecnica/|access-date=10 August 2021|website=Jmania.it|language=it|archive-date=10 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210810200807/https://jmania.it/cristian-romero-scheda-tecnica/|url-status=live}}</ref> Romero was promoted to [[Argentine Primera División]] side [[Club Atlético Belgrano|Belgrano]]'s first team in 2016;<ref name="Belgrano pro deal">{{cite news|title=Cristian Romero firmó su primer contrato|url=http://www.belgranocordoba.com/noticia-belgrano/1684/|website=Club Atlético Belgrano|date=27 May 2016|access-date=15 April 2017|language=es|archive-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420112124/https://www.belgranocordoba.com/noticia-belgrano/1684/|url-status=live}}</ref> his debut came on 28 August, in a league match with [[Club Atlético Independiente|Independiente]].<ref name="Soccerway profile">{{Soccerway|433963|access-date=15 April 2017}}</ref> One month later, Romero played in both of Belgrano's [[2016 Copa Sudamericana]] round of 16 draws against [[Coritiba Foot Ball Club|Coritiba]].<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> In two seasons with Belgrano's first-team, he made nineteen appearances in all competitions.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/>

===Genoa===
In July 2018, Romero joined [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]] of [[Serie A]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=I nuovi stranieri della Serie A: Cristian Romero (Genoa)|url=https://www.spaziocalcio.it/approfondimento/schede-giocatori/i-nuovi-stranieri-della-serie-a-cristian-romero-genoa/|website=Spazio Calcio|access-date=6 May 2024|language=it}}</ref> He scored his first senior goal in his second Genoa match, netting in a 2–2 draw with [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] on 28 October, only to be sent off later.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/>

=== Juventus ===
On 9 July 2019, [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] announced Romero was having a medical ahead of a requested transfer.<ref name="JUV1">{{Cite news|title=Cristian Romero begins Juventus medical|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2019/cristian-romero-begins-juventus-medical.php|website=Juventus|date=9 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709101414/https://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2019/cristian-romero-begins-juventus-medical.php|archive-date=9 July 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==== Return to Genoa (loan) ====
On 12 July 2019, Juventus announced the permanent acquisition of Romero from Genoa for €26&nbsp;million, with the player remaining at his former club on loan for the rest of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Romero, gli accordi con il Genoa|url=http://www.juventus.com/it/news/news/2019/romero--gli-accordi-con-il-genoa.php|website=Juventus|access-date=12 July 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712183711/https://www.juventus.com/it/news/news/2019/romero--gli-accordi-con-il-genoa.php|archive-date=12 July 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>

=== Atalanta ===
On 5 September 2020, Romero joined [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]] on loan until 30 June 2022 with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://m.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/ufficiale-juve-ceduto-romero-in-prestito-biennale-con-diritto-di-riscatto-all-atalanta-1428834 |title=Ufficiale: Juve, ceduto Romero in prestito biennale con diritto di riscatto all'Atalanta |date=5 September 2020 |website=Tutto Mercato Web |language=it |access-date=5 September 2020 |archive-date=9 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210609165156/https://m.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/ufficiale-juve-ceduto-romero-in-prestito-biennale-con-diritto-di-riscatto-all-atalanta-1428834 |url-status=live }}</ref> He was elected the best defender of the [[2020–21 Serie A]] season.<ref name="Tottenham"/>

===Tottenham Hotspur===
[[File:Cuti Romero Tottenham 2022.jpg|upright|thumb|right|Romero with Spurs in March 2022]]
On 6 August 2021, Juventus announced that Atalanta had activated the option to sign Romero for €16&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Esercizio del Diritto di Opzione per Il Calciatore Cristian Romero|url=https://www.juventus.com/it/news/articoli/esercizio-del-diritto-di-opzione-per-il-calciatore-cristian-romero|website=Juventus|access-date=6 August 2021|language=it|archive-date=24 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231024043424/https://www.juventus.com/it/news/articoli/esercizio-del-diritto-di-opzione-per-il-calciatore-cristian-romero|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that day, [[Premier League]] club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] announced his signing from Atalanta on an initial season-long loan with an option to make the deal permanent.<ref name="Tottenham">{{Cite web|title=Romero signs from Atalanta|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2021/august/romero-signs-from-atalanta/|publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|date=6 August 2021|access-date=6 August 2021|archive-date=24 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231024042924/https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2021/august/romero-signs-from-atalanta/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Cristian Romero joins Tottenham Hotspur|url=https://www.atalanta.it/en/news/cristian-romero-joins-tottenham-hotspur/|website=Atalanta BC|date=6 August 2021|access-date=6 August 2021|archive-date=24 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231024041649/https://www.atalanta.it/en/news/cristian-romero-joins-tottenham-hotspur/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Romero debuted for the club on 15 August, coming on as a late substitute for [[Pierre-Emile Højbjerg]] in a match against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] that Tottenham won 1–0.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Simon|last=Burnton|title=Tottenham 1–0 Manchester City: Premier League, as it happened|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/aug/15/tottenham-v-manchester-city-premier-league-live|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=15 August 2021|access-date=22 August 2021|archive-date=24 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231024042721/https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/aug/15/tottenham-v-manchester-city-premier-league-live|url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 August 2021, he made his first start in the [[UEFA Europa Conference League]] first leg tie against [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]], which ended in a 1–0 defeat.<ref>{{cite news|first=Richard|last=Morgan|title=Pacos de Ferreira 1–0 Tottenham: Much-changed Spurs lose Europa Conference League play-off first-leg tie|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/pacos-ferreira-vs-tottenham-hotspur/457263|website=[[Sky Sports]]|date=20 August 2021|access-date=22 August 2021|archive-date=24 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231024042904/https://www.skysports.com/football/pacos-ferreira-vs-tottenham-hotspur/457263|url-status=live}}</ref> Romero scored his first goal for Tottenham in a 2–0 victory over [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]]. On 30 August 2022, he signed for Tottenham permanently with a contract lasting until 2027.<ref>{{cite news|title=Romero completes permanent move|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2022/august/romero-completes-permanent-move/|publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|date=30 August 2022|access-date=30 August 2022|archive-date=26 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230326210845/https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2022/august/romero-completes-permanent-move/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Ahead of the [[2023–24 Premier League|2023–24 Premier League season]], Romero was named as one of Tottenham's vice-captains.<ref>{{cite news|first=Charlie|last=Eccleshare|title=Tottenham's new leadership group: Can they provide what is so badly needed?|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4777101/2023/08/16/tottenham-son-captain-maddison-romero-leadership/|website=[[The Athletic]]|date=16 August 2023|access-date=10 November 2023}}</ref> He made a strong start to the season, being described by manager [[Ange Postecoglou]] as the "rock" in Tottenham's defence, and earning a nomination for the Player of the Month award in October.<ref>{{cite news|title=Romero shortlisted for October's Premier League Player of the Month award|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2023/november/romero-shortlisted-for-octobers-premier-league-player-of-the-month-award/|publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|access-date=10 November 2023|archive-date=10 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231110123309/https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2023/november/romero-shortlisted-for-octobers-premier-league-player-of-the-month-award/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Tottenham: Ange Postecoglou praises Cristian Romero|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/c974d98pj1jo|work=BBC Sport|date=4 November 2023|access-date=10 November 2023|archive-date=10 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231110123306/https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/c974d98pj1jo|url-status=live}}</ref> However, on 6 November 2023, Romero was shown a straight red card during Tottenham's 4–1 loss to rivals [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Tim|last=Spiers|title=Cristian Romero's 'red mist' has cost Spurs yet again, he simply has to learn|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5039060/2023/11/08/tottenham-romero-red-card-disciplinary/|website=The Athletic|date=8 November 2023|access-date=10 November 2023|archive-date=10 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231110123307/https://theathletic.com/5039060/2023/11/08/tottenham-romero-red-card-disciplinary/|url-status=live}}</ref> It was his fourth red card since moving to the Premier League, more than any other player in that time.<ref>{{cite news|title=Romero's red card turned the tide|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/tottenham-chelsea-live-score-updates-result-premier-league/vOYPAJ7n7rXR/uxk7SlUe2ME6/|website=[[The Athletic]]|date=7 November 2023 |access-date=10 November 2023|archive-date=10 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231110123307/https://theathletic.com/live-blogs/tottenham-chelsea-live-score-updates-result-premier-league/vOYPAJ7n7rXR/uxk7SlUe2ME6/|url-status=live}}</ref> Romero scored on his return from suspension, Tottenham's only goal in a 2–1 loss to [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=West Ham's Moyes celebrates "one of the biggest wins"|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67574361|website=BBC Sport|access-date=8 December 2023|archive-date=7 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231207233705/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67574361|url-status=live}}</ref>

Romero played the entire [[2025 UEFA Europa League final]], securing a 1–0 win against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]. He was awarded Player of the Match for his performance, winning his first club honour, Tottenham Hotspur's first major trophy in [[2008 Football League Cup final|17 years]] and their first European trophy in [[1984 UEFA Cup final|41 years]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Blitz |first=Sam |date=21 May 2025 |title=Spurs 1–0 Man Utd player ratings: Cristian Romero produces captain's performance in Europa League final |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/13372256/spurs-1-0-man-utd-player-ratings-cristian-romero-produces-captains-performance-in-europa-league-final |access-date=22 May 2025 |work=Sky Sports}}</ref>

Ahead of the [[2025–26 Premier League|2025–26 Premier League season]], Romero was named Tottenham captain by new Spurs manager [[Thomas Frank (football manager)|Thomas Frank]] after the departure of [[Son Heung-min]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Thomas Frank names Cristian Romero as captain |url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2025/august/thomas-frank-names-cristian-romero-as-captain/ |access-date=13 August 2025 |publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.}}</ref> Shortly after being named captain, he renewed his Tottenham contract until 2029.<ref>{{cite news |title=New deal for Cristian Romero |url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2025/august/new-deal-for-cristian-romero/ |date=18 August 2025 |access-date=19 August 2025 |publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.}}</ref> On 2 December, Romero scored twice, including a [[bicycle kick]] equaliser in stoppage time, in a 2–2 draw against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Newcastle United 2–2 Tottenham Hotspur |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cr7lv773lr9t |date=2 December 2025 |access-date=5 December 2025 |work=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> On 20 December, Romero received a second yellow card as he was sent off during Tottenham's 2–1 loss to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] for kicking at [[Ibrahima Konaté]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Romero wouldn't have seen red if referee 'did his job' - Frank|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c0l9yng296xo |date=20 December 2025 |access-date=20 December 2025 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref> A second red card of the season for Romero came in a 2–0 loss to Manchester United on 7 February 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Stone |first=Simon |date=7 February 2026 |title=Cristian Romero red card: Tottenham captain's week ends in 'perfect storm' |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c87r7nzxl0zo |access-date=9 February 2026 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

Throughout his time at Tottenham, Romero became known for outspoken comments in the media, criticising the club's leadership, particularly for their transfer strategy amidst multiple injury crises.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Law |first=Matt |last2=Dean |first2=Sam |date=10 December 2024 |title=Cristian Romero apologises for blaming Tottenham board for on-pitch failures |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2024/12/10/cristian-romero-criticise-tottenham-board-transfer-spending/ |access-date=9 February 2026 |work=The Telegraph |language=en-GB |issn=0307-1235}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Hytner |first=David |date=2 February 2026 |title=Romero hits out at Spurs’ ‘disgraceful’ squad shortage on social media post |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/feb/02/christian-romero-tottenham-manchester-city-disgraceful-squad-shortage-social-media-post |access-date=9 February 2026 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He sustained a knee injury in a 1–0 away defeat against [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] on 12 April 2026, ruling him out for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://global.espn.com/football/story/_/id/48474970/Message |title=Tottenham defender Cristian Romero out for remainder of the season - sources |publisher=ESPN |date=13 April 2026 }}</ref> Controversy escalated further in May 2026 when Romero travelled to Argentina during Tottenham's survival fight, choosing to attend Belgrano's title-deciding clash against [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] instead of remaining with Spurs for their crucial Premier League finale against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{cite web |last=McAleer |first=Ben |url=https://talksport.com/football/4275726/cristian-romero-river-plate-belgrano-decision-tottenham-everton/ |title=Cristian Romero ‘couldn’t care less’ as Tottenham captain decides to skip Premier League relegation decider |publisher=talkSPORT |date=21 May 2026 }}</ref> However, he appeared at the [[Tottenham Hotspur Stadium]] before kick-off after widespread backlash over his trip.<ref>{{cite web |last=Telfer |first=Alastair |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c1k2r04k1r2o |title=Spurs captain Romero back in England for final game |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Romero has represented Argentina at the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|U20]] level, winning seven caps at the [[2017 South American U-20 Championship]] in Ecuador.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> In April 2017, he was called up for Argentina's training camp ahead of the [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in South Korea but was not selected on the tournament squad list.<ref name="Arg U20s camp">{{cite news|title=Lista para la semana que viene|url=http://afa.com.ar/7040/lista-para-la-semana-que-viene|access-date=15 April 2017|website=Argentine Football Association|date=15 April 2017|language=es|archive-date=16 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170416125423/http://afa.com.ar/7040/lista-para-la-semana-que-viene|url-status=live}}</ref> Romero was called up for the [[Argentina national under-23 football team|U23s]] in September 2019.<ref name="AFA1">{{Cite news|title=La Selección Sub 23 jugará ante Bolivia desde las 19, en el estadio de Banfield|url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/la-seleccion-sub-23-enfrentara-a-bolivia-desde-las-19-en-el-estadio-de-banfield|website=AFA|date=3 September 2019|access-date=4 September 2019|language=es|archive-date=19 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201119141250/https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/la-seleccion-sub-23-enfrentara-a-bolivia-desde-las-19-en-el-estadio-de-banfield|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Senior===
On 3 June 2021, Romero debuted for the [[Argentina national football team|senior national team]] a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Chile national football team|Chile]], playing the full match.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Cristian Romero, la novedad que se ganó el puesto y ahora tendrá su debut mundialista en Qatar 2022|url=https://www.tycsports.com/seleccion-argentina/cristian-cuti-romero-seleccion-argentina-mundial-qatar-2022-id452652.html|website=[[TyC Sports]]|date=11 November 2022|language=es|access-date=6 May 2024|archive-date=6 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240506134331/https://www.tycsports.com/seleccion-argentina/cristian-cuti-romero-seleccion-argentina-mundial-qatar-2022-id452652.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In his second game for Argentina on 8 June, he scored his first international goal, coming from a thumping header against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] after only 130 seconds. This goal also broke the record for the fastest ever scored for Argentina in a professional match, surpassing [[Diego Maradona]]'s goal after 168 seconds against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]] in 1985.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Πέρασε τον Μαραντόνα και... έγραψε ιστορία ο Ρομέρο!|trans-title=Romero surpassed Maradona... and made history!|url=https://www.sport-fm.gr/article/podosfairo/prokrimatika%20mountial/romero-perase-ton-maradona-kai-egrapse-istoria/4183845|website=Sport FM Greece|date=9 June 2021|access-date=9 June 2021|language=el|archive-date=9 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210609130832/https://www.sport-fm.gr/article/podosfairo/prokrimatika%20mountial/romero-perase-ton-maradona-kai-egrapse-istoria/4183845|url-status=live}}</ref>

In June 2021, Romero was included in [[Lionel Scaloni]]'s final Argentina 28-man squad for the [[2021 Copa América]]<ref>{{cite web |url = https://en.as.com/en/2021/06/14/football/1623671691_620875.html |title = Argentina National Team Squad 2021 |website=[[Diario AS]]|date = 15 June 2021 |access-date = 11 July 2021|language=es|archive-date = 29 June 2021 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210629163051/https://en.as.com/en/2021/06/14/football/1623671691_620875.html |url-status = dead }}</ref> and the Team of the Tournament at the end as Argentina won the competition.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Uno por uno, el equipo ideal de la CONMEBOL Copa América 2021 elegido por el GET|url=https://copaamerica.com/es/noticias/equipo-ideal-get-conmebol-copa-america-2021/ |website=Copa América |date=13 July 2021|access-date=27 March 2022|language=es |archive-date=14 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210714034039/https://copaamerica.com/es/noticias/equipo-ideal-get-conmebol-copa-america-2021/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> Romero was also an integral part of the Argentinian team which won the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], in which he started in six out of seven matches including the final.<ref>{{Cite news|title="I watch it every day!", Tottenham defender Romero admits he's still not over Argentina's World Cup final win over France|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/christian-romero-watches-world-cup-final-daily/blt53d70f31b7bee1f5|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=5 February 2023|access-date=8 August 2023|archive-date=10 August 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230810230214/https://www.goal.com/en/news/christian-romero-watches-world-cup-final-daily/blt53d70f31b7bee1f5|url-status=live}}</ref>

In June 2024, Romero was included in Scaloni's final 26-man Argentina squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=15 June 2024 |title=Lionel Scaloni dio a conocer la lista de la Selección argentina para la Copa América 2024 |url=https://tn.com.ar/deportes/futbol/2024/06/15/lionel-scaloni-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-la-seleccion-argentina-para-la-copa-america-2024/?gad_source=1&gclid=CjwKCAjwqf20BhBwEiwAt7dtdeK13_I24H4iqEBua7UtmDLn6_x-FfDm-gzEseLS8vJCnOlmjC3PlBoCHEwQAvD_BwE |access-date=23 July 2024 |work=Todo Noticias}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Romero has been described as a "proactive" defender always playing on the "front foot." This allows him to step up in the backline and make crucial interceptions in midfield. He is well known for his decision-making in his risky style of play. Romero is also known for his exceptional ability in the air and is adept at scoring headers in the box.
<ref>{{Cite news|title=Cristian Romero: Total Player Report|url=https://tactical-times.com/cristian-romero-total-player-report/|website=The Tactical Times|access-date=16 February 2024|archive-date=16 February 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240216175611/https://tactical-times.com/cristian-romero-total-player-report/|url-status=live}}</ref>

